{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CBchhnYE5Ks69HxHXqB1Py","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my findings. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of Functions and Sections in title-extractor.ts\n\n### 1. **applyBlindOcrRepair**\n- **Line Range:** 833–862\n- **Signature:** `function applyBlindOcrRepair(text: string): string`\n- **Key Code:** Handles two paths—all-caps text with aggressive digit→letter replacements (1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S, ¡→I, €→E, ÍÌ→I), and mixed-case text split by whitespace with token-specific repairs (1→l in lowercase contexts, etc.)\n\n### 2. **buildCandidates**\n- **Line Range:** 538–718\n- **Signature:** `function buildCandidates(lines: Array<string>): { candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }>; burstEnd: number }`\n- **OCR Repair Block (near line index ≤ 5):** Lines 658–671\n  - Checks if `line.index <= 5 && OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(line.text)`\n  - Calls `applyBlindOcrRepair()` to generate additional candidate with clean version\n  - Only adds if result differs and passes hard filters\n\n### 3. **Direct-Successor Bonus Logic**\n- **Line Range:** 1069–1089\n- **Location:** Inside the scoring phase of the main `extractTitle` function\n- **Key Code:** \n  - Iterates top 3 candidates (`ci <= 2`)\n  - Checks if previous line (`candidate.position - 1`) is a section label, metadata, or pipe-separated line\n  - Adds `+0.10` to score, baseScore, and thresholdScore if true\n  - Capped with other positional bonuses at `maxPositionalBoost = 0.15` (lines 1091–1098)\n\n### 4. **OVERFLOW_MARKERS Regex**\n- **Line:** 436\n- **Definition:** \n  ```typescript\n  const OVERFLOW_MARKERS = /\\b(PREVIOUS\\s+(RECIPE|PAGE)\\s+(OVERFLOW|CONTENT)|SPILLOVER|CONTINUATION|CORRUPTED\\s+SECTION)\\b/i;\n  ```\n- **Used in:** `findBurstEnd()` to skip preambles from synthetic multi-page OCR\n\n### 5. **findBurstEnd**\n- **Line Range:** 431–507\n- **Signature:** `function findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number`\n- **Key Logic:**\n  - Skips overflow preambles (lines 434–473)\n  - Skips garbled lines < 20 chars (line 475)\n  - Skips cooking instruction prologues (3+ consecutive lines, lines 478–488)\n  - Skips prose prologues with lowercase start, commas, or sentence endings (lines 489–505)\n\n### 6. **isTitleAbsentPage**\n- **Line Range:** 370–382\n- **Signature:** `function isTitleAbsentPage(lines: Array<string>): boolean`\n- **Key Logic:** Returns true if first 3 non-empty lines are ALL ingredients, cooking instructions, or body prose (suggests OCR started mid-recipe with no title)\n\n### 7. **generateBlindOcrVariants**\n- **Status:** Does not exist in the file\n\n### 8. **hasErraticCasing**\n- **Status:** Does not exist in the file\n\n### 9. **passesHardFilters**\n- **Line Range:** 384–425\n- **Signature:** `function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean`\n- **Key Checks:**\n  - Length 3–80 chars\n  - Not ingredient, metadata, cooking instruction, or garbled\n  - Not prefixed by number, pipe-separated, slash-breadcrumbs, bullet-list\n  - Not sub-section headers (\"For the...\", trailing `:`)\n  - Not page reference or corrupted spillover annotation\n  - Not square-bracket category tags\n  - Not section label\n  - Not single NON_TITLE_WORD\n  - Not ≥8 words without `+`, `:`, `&`, `/` separators\n\n### 10. **isSectionLabel**\n- **Line Range:** 190–197\n- **Signature:** `function isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean`\n- **Key Logic:** Normalizes text (strip diacritics, remove trailing `:/.`), checks against `SECTION_LABELS` set, also checks for OCR variant where leading `l` may be corrupted `I` (e.g., \"lngredients\")\n\n### 11. **looksLikeCookingInstruction**\n- **Line Range:** 348–354\n- **Signature:** `function looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean`\n- **Key Logic:**\n  - Requires ≥4 words\n  - Matches `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` or `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` patterns\n\n---\n\n**File path:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab32e537c2d7211ff (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 92836\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 63555</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e11d10e0-5bff-40d6-8c5d-c73d1cbcdcc2","uuid":"fd902453-884f-4676-a545-a1f4cc941bab","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts, find the line numbers and signatures of these functions/sections:\n1. `applyBlindOcrRepair` \n2. `buildCandidates` (especially the OCR repair block near line index <= 5)\n3. The direct-successor bonus logic\n4. `OVERFLOW_MARKERS` regex\n5. `findBurstEnd` function\n6. `isTitleAbsentPage` function\n7. `generateBlindOcrVariants` if it exists\n8. `hasErraticCasing` if it exists\n9. `passesHardFilters`\n10. `isSectionLabel`\n11. `looksLikeCookingInstruction`\n\nFor each, give me the line number range and key code. Be thorough - read the full file if needed.","agentId":"ab32e537c2d7211ff","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my findings. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of Functions and Sections in title-extractor.ts\n\n### 1. **applyBlindOcrRepair**\n- **Line Range:** 833–862\n- **Signature:** `function applyBlindOcrRepair(text: string): string`\n- **Key Code:** Handles two paths—all-caps text with aggressive digit→letter replacements (1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S, ¡→I, €→E, ÍÌ→I), and mixed-case text split by whitespace with token-specific repairs (1→l in lowercase contexts, etc.)\n\n### 2. **buildCandidates**\n- **Line Range:** 538–718\n- **Signature:** `function buildCandidates(lines: Array<string>): { candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }>; burstEnd: number }`\n- **OCR Repair Block (near line index ≤ 5):** Lines 658–671\n  - Checks if `line.index <= 5 && OCR_ARTI